OL,3,CJersey's new first-time buyer scheme
OL,4,Conly likely to help around 60 people
OL,6,FWhen asked how many people will
OL,7,Fbenefit from the plans Deputy Mezec
OL,8,Fsaid: "In the first few tranches a
OL,9,Fmaximum of 60 (households) probably.
OL,10,FBut that gives us a really good
OL,11,Fopportunity to measure how much of a
OL,12,Fsuccess it is first time round. What
OL,13,Fkinds of people benefit from it and if
OL,14,Fthere are tweaks we need to make.
OL,16,F"If it proves to be popular and proves
OL,17,Fto be successful then I'm going to
OL,18,Fwant to push to get some more funding
OL,19,Ffor it, so we can keep rolling the
OL,20,Fscheme and keep supporting more
OL,21,Fpeople."
