OL,3,CJersey's new first-time buyer scheme
OL,4,Conly likely to help around 60 people
OL,6,FThe plans would consist of a shared
OL,7,Fequity scheme with the government
OL,8,Fgetting a part of the profits when the
OL,9,Fproperty is sold in the future.
OL,11,FOn whether Deputy Mezec thought using
OL,12,F#10 million of public money to help
OL,13,Fjust 60 households, he argued that the
OL,14,Fscheme had potential to grow:
OL,15,F"There'll be greater value for money
OL,16,Fover time because when those people
OL,17,Fsell those homes, when they're ready
OL,18,Fto move on to their second home, the
OL,19,Fuplift in the value of the property,
OL,20,Fwe'll get our share back from that.
